			<outline text="April 1" created="Tue, 01 Apr 2008 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="11 years of Scripting News" created="Wed, 02 Apr 2008 01:29:31 GMT" name="11YearsOfScriptingNews" type="outline">
					<outline text="To mark the 11th anniversary of Scripting News, here's a pointer to docs on the software I used to edit the site. " created="Wed, 02 Apr 2008 01:29:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="http://www.scripting.com/frontier/netscripting/newsPage.html " created="Wed, 02 Apr 2008 01:30:16 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I thought of what eventually became the weblog as a News Page, a roughly reverse chronologic list of links to news stories. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/frontier/gifs/newsPageOutline.gif&quot;&gt;Then&lt;/a&gt; as now I edited using the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/frontier/snippets/outlinerCribSheet.html&quot;&gt;outliner&lt;/a&gt; in Frontier. " created="Wed, 02 Apr 2008 01:31:51 GMT"/>
					<outline text="We made the NewsPage suite and all the other code that ran in the Frontier environment (the &quot;Aretha&quot; release) available in source to anyone who wanted to use it, and amazingly, a fair number of sites poppped up that more or less followed the pattern of Scripting News." created="Wed, 02 Apr 2008 01:30:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I don't remember them all, but the most notable one (to me) was Robot Wisdom, which was managed for the first few years with this software." created="Wed, 02 Apr 2008 01:30:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There will be people who give me a hard time for writing this, but that's their problem not mine. One of the benefits of creating something that really took off is that you get to gloat about it. &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Wed, 02 Apr 2008 01:34:02 GMT"/>
					</outline>
